text: Mal'ak (also spelled Malak, Melek) may refer to: * Malak Hifni Nasif (1886-1918), Egyptian feminist and poet * Malak Karsh (1915–2001), Canadian photographer * Malak, Northern Territory a suburb in the City of Darwin, Australia * Mal'ak Elohim or angel of the Lord * Darth Malak, a character from the fictional Star Wars universe ==See also== * Angels in Judaism * Malach (disambiguation) * Malik (disambiguation) * Malakh, a Somali title meaning war leader * Melek (disambiguation) Category:Arabic unisex given names
title: Malak
